August 20th update, today they are finishing laying and cutting the turf for the main field area! Next up they will be working on the sidelines followed by inserting the hashmarks and numbers which will take a considerable amount of time and is all weather permitting! LET’S GO CHIPPEWA!

post_text: July 31st update on the Chippewa Facilities Project!
text: July 31st update on the Chippewa Facilities Project!

post_text:
Finally, warm and dry weather for the Summer of 2019. Unfortunately, the wet weather in May and June put the Stadium Field Turf Project behind schedule. We are currently targeting September 6, 2019 as our grand opening. The pictures being posted show a flat stabilized base and we are ready for the drainage system to be installed starting Monday, August 5. This should take a week to 10 days. A final grade takes place to ensure the field is perfect before the turf is installed. Then the turf will be installed which takes 2-3 weeks.
I want to Thank everyone for their financial support. This project is in its initial phase but the support and has been fantastic. This project is a true testimony to the Power of US!
A new locker room facility for the kids, updated and lighted tennis courts, and several other projects will be taking place as we continue to transform our athletic facilities. Thank you for your support.

Todd S. Osborn
Superintendent

post_text: Did you drive by the fields yet? Check out all of the progress already! Thank you to everyone who is helping to make this project a reality for Chippewa Local Schools students!
text: Did you drive by the fields yet? Check out all of the progress already! Thank you to everyone who is helping to make this project a reality for Chippewa Local Schools students!

post_text:
Construction has finally started at the stadium. If you would like a more detailed information as to the process that will be happening please click on the following link: http://www.fieldturf.eu/en/the-fieldturf-difference/how-it-works

Mr. Justin Williams and Mr. Ron Dannemiller have made donations to the stadium project. Mr. Williams has provided all the trucking needed to move the dirt out of the stadium. This will be around 400 loads of dirt. Mr. Dannemiller will supply the underground conduit and complete the wiring for a new sound system. Thank you Mr. Williams and Mr. Dannemiller for making a difference in the lives of the student-athletes in Chippewa.

The 500 Club is growing and I personally want to thank all those that have made donations. Go Chipps!

Todd S. Osborn
Superintendent

post_text:
Frequently Asked Questions
1. When will the construction start at the new stadium? The contractor, Vasco, will determine the start date for construction. They will need a period of 1-2 weeks of fairly dry weather, so they are able to remove 9 inches of topsoil, and get the ground compacted and drainage installed. The anticipated date to start is the middle of June, weather permitting.
2. Our financial graphs posted show the district's current revenue and expenditures.
3. Chippewa Local Schools has not received any grant money to date.
